33","Bayencourt, 80057, Somme, Picardie, France":"Bayencourt, Somme, Picardie, Frankrig"},"nl":{"ABT 1107–ABT 1172":"circa 1107–circa 1172","1105–Female":"1105–Overleden","1107–1172":"1107–1172","1116–1165":"1116–1165","1133–1189":"1133–1189","1077–1135":"1077–1135","1089–1147":"1089–1147","1132":"1132","ABT 1147":"circa 1147","1077":"1077","1165":"1165","ABT 1107":"circa 1107","1172":"1172","ABT 1172":"circa 1172","1107":"1107","1105":"1105","1116":"1116","ABT 1165":"circa 1165","1147":"1147","ABT 1133":"circa 1133","1135":"1135","1189":"1189","ABT 1135":"circa 1135","1089":"1089","1133":"1133","Bayencourt, 80057, Somme, Picardie, France":"Bayencourt, Somme, Picardie, Frankrijk"},"en":{"ABT 1107–ABT 1172":"about 1107–about 1172","1105–Female":"1105–Deceased","1107–1172":"1107–1172","1116–1165":"1116–1165","1133–1189":"1133–1189","1077–1135":"1077–1135","1089–1147":"1089–1147","1132":"1132","ABT 1147":"about 1147","1077":"1077","1165":"1165","ABT 1107":"about 1107","1172":"1172","ABT 1172":"about 1172","1107":"1107","1105":"1105","1116":"1116","ABT 1165":"about 1165","1147":"1147","ABT 1133":"about 1133","1135":"1135","1189":"1189","ABT 1135":"about 1135","1089":"1089","1133":"1133","Bayencourt, 80057, Somme, Picardie, France":"Bayencourt, Somme, Picardie, France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Nocher","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["French: topographic name denoting someone who lived in a rocky place, from <i>rocher</i> ‘rock, crag, boulder’, or a habitational name from a place called Rocher. Compare   Durocher  .","Altered form of French   Desrochers  .","History: Pierre Desrochers/Rocher from Saint-Macoux in Vienne, France, married Suzanne Rabouin in Batiscan, QC, in 1696."],"variants":[{"name":"Rocheleau","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Marcel, Armand, Alphonse, Andre, Normand, Aurore, Cecile, Elphege, Emile, Fernand, Gilles, Mathieu.","Altered form of French <b>Rochereau</b>: topographic name from a diminutive of <i>rocher</i> ‘rock, crag, boulder’ (see   Rocher  ), or a habitational name from (Le) Rochereau, the name of several places in the western part of France. Compare   Rushlow  ."]},{"name":"Rochon","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Pierre, Andre, Aurele, Gaston, Michel, Yves, Adrien, Antoine, Fernande, Gaetan, Germain, Gilles.","Altered form of French <b>Rocheron</b>: topographic name from a diminutive of <i>rocher</i> ‘rock, crag, boulder’ (see   Rocher  ), or a habitational name from Le Rocheron, the name of two places in Indre-et-Loire.","French: diminutive of   Roche   ‘rock’."]},{"name":"Durocher","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Andre, Fernand, Gilles, Marcel, Normand, Alain, Antoine, Armand, Bibiane, Emile, Emilien, Gaetan.","French: topographic name from <i>rocher</i> ‘rock, crag, boulder’, with fused preposition and definite article <i>du</i> ‘from the’, denoting someone who lived in a rocky place; or a habitational name for someone from Le Rocher, the name of several places in various parts of France. Compare   Derusha   and   Rocher  .","Altered form of French   Desrochers  , a cognate of 1 above."]}]},{"name":"II","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Loving’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Nocher II Bayencourt was born about 1107, in Bayencourt, Somme, Picardie, France, his father, Collard Bayencourt, was 31 and his mother, Adelaide Heilly, was 20. He married Giselberthe Bailescourt in 1132. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died about 1172, at the age of 67."},"et":{"ABT 1107–ABT 1172":"umbes 1107–umbes 1172","1105–Female":"1105–Surnud","1107–1172":"1107–1172","1116–1165":"1116–1165","1133–1189":"1133–1189","1077–1135":"1077–1135","1089–1147":"1089–1147","1132":"1132","ABT 1147":"umbes 1147","1077":"1077","1165":"1165","ABT 1107":"umbes 1107","1172":"1172","ABT 1172":"umbes 11